NATIONWIDE CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL CHAMPIONSHIP
September 23, 2015
Kip Eriksen
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
 Q.  To bring this back here for another three years - we've seen it nothing but grow in the past - what's in the future for this?  
KIP ERIKSEN: Hopefully a lot more growth.  It was a great process for us to go through as this current contract came to an end.  Had a chance to go back to all our partners and reaffirm the direction we're going.   
It was unanimous support to keep going, growing the event, keep building a great experience for golf fans in Central Ohio.   
Equally as important, keep growing our revenue so we can continue to donate more money each year to Nationwide Children's Hospital and their pediatric cancer program.   
Just a great reaffirmation of the work we've been doing to be able to continue it with our partners.   
 Q.  You guys have been the king of promotions.  Any crazy ones this year?  
KIP ERIKSEN: We are going to keep riding out the Birdie Time is Miller Time play.  It's extremely popular out at the 13th hole.  Every time a player makes a birdie, we turn the shot clock on for 15 minutes.  Beers are $1.  Great, festive atmosphere out there.   
Got a bunch of TVs so people can watch college football throughout the day on Saturday, NFL on Sunday, watch some great golf as well, and just enjoy the atmosphere.  So we're excited about that one again.   
  
   
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT